Release Notes_1001_
\layout Standard

This is the another public release of Mahogany.
 As with usual we make the source available and binaries for the most common
 operating systems supported.
 Mahogany should generally work on any Unix flavour.
 This time, we do not include a Windows version, as our main Windows developer
 has been busy working on wxWindows over the last weeks.
 He is now catching up and we hope to release a common Windows and Unix
 version (0.51) within few weeks.
 Finally, work on making Mahogany available for MacOS is in progress.
\layout Standard

Due to the fact that it is a cross-platform effort, the compilation and
 make system are a bit more complex than the average package.
 However, the source code is provided and you can attempt to compile it
 yourself.
 If you are trying to port it to a new platform, let us know and we will
 be happy to help you.
\layout Subsection

Changes against the previous version
\layout Subsubsection

0.5 against 0.23a
\layout Standard

This release has long been delayed, mainly due to us waiting for changes
 in wxWindows to be completed.
 As we introduced new features in the meantime, those introduced new delays,
 and so on.
 It has been more than half a year since the last release, so changes are
 major.
 We hope to stick to a much faster cycle of minor update releases for the
 future.
 The main new features are:
\layout Itemize

Proper support for MH folders.
\layout Itemize

Browsing and subscription management for IMAP and NNTP servers.
\layout Itemize

A plugin module system has been created which allows to dynamically load
 expansion modules.
 Existing modules (statically linked in this release, but dynamically linkable)
 include a filtering language and PalmOS support.
 For the future, a calendar/timeplanner plugin is planned.
\layout Itemize

Configurable filtering rules have been added.
\layout Itemize

Message threading and configurable sort order is supported.
\layout Itemize

An HTML-based help browser has been added.
 
\layout Itemize

Configurable date format.
\layout Itemize

Handling of dial-up networking and detection of connection status.
\layout Itemize

Optional user of a Trash folder.
\layout Itemize

Wizard-dialogs and 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset 

tip of the day
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset 

 dialogs added to make Mahogany easier to use.
\layout Itemize

Optional SSL support can be compiled in (not activated by default due to
 US export restrictions), allowing secure access to mail and news servers.
\layout Itemize

PalmOS handheld connectivity: synchronise e-mails with your PalmOS handheld
 computer and use its addressbook within Mahogany.
 Also, backup, restore and install databases of your handheld.
\layout Itemize

Bug fixes in nearly all parts of the code.
 Mahogany should suffer much less from crashes than earlier versions.
 The message editor behaves better and is faster.
\layout Itemize

Minor GUI improvements like keyboard bindings and nicer icons.
 Support for KDE and GNOME filetype icons.
\layout Subsubsection

