 Mahogany.
 In a seaparate dialog (
\begin_inset LatexCommand \ref{FolderFiltersDialog}

\end_inset 

) you can then pick any rule from the list and assign it to a folder.
 As you can have different sets of rules for each folder and might want
 to share rules for some folders, this dialog simply sets up rules and you
 can later specify for which folders to use them.
 When editing or adding a new filter rule, you will get to the following
 dialog:
\layout Subsubsection

The Filter-Rule Dialog_4261_
\layout Standard

This dialog allows you to set up or edit an individual filtering rule, it
 contains of the following components:
\layout Itemize

The rule name, in the text entry field at the very top.
 This name is only to help you remember what the rule does and will appear
 in the list of rules in the main Filters Dialog, but is without any further
 significance.
\layout Itemize

Underneath the name, you find the text 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset 

If Message...
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset 

 followed by at least one row of conditioncontrols.
\layout Itemize

Under the condition controls you find the text 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset 

Then do this:
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset 

 followed by some action controls.
\layout Standard

You can add more pattern matching controls by pressing the [More] button,
 and you can delete the last pattern matching rule by pressing the [Less]
 button.
 The number of actions to execute is fixed to one.
\layout Standard

You can use several condition and connect them via logical AND and OR, optionall
y negating them by ticking the [Not] box.
 The following conditions can be tested for at present:
\layout Itemize

Always - this rule will always be executed
\layout Itemize

Contains - check if the text next to it is contained in the message component
 selected
\layout Itemize

Match - check if the message component selected is exactly this text (case
 independent)
\layout Itemize

Match Case - check if the message compent selected is exactly this text
 (case dependent)
\layout Itemize

Match RegExp - check if the message compent selected matches the regular
 expression specified
\layout Itemize

Larger Than - check if the message is larger than this in KByte
\layout Itemize

Smaller Than - check if the message is smaller than this in KByte
\layout Itemize

Older Than - check if the message is older than this many days
\layout Itemize

Newer Than - check if the message is newer than this many days
\layout Itemize

Is SPAM - check if the message originates from a system blacklisted as sending
 unsolicited emails (SPAM).
 
\layout Itemize

Python - execute the text in the box in the built-in Python interpreter
 and proceed if it returns a non-0 result.
\layout Standard

The possible actions which can be performed, are:
\layout Itemize

Delete - deletes the message
\layout Itemize

Copy to - copies the message to the folder specified
\layout Itemize

Move to - moves the message to the folder specified
\layout Itemize

Expunge - expunge all messages in this folder
\layout Itemize

MessageBox - open a message box dialog with the text specified
\layout Itemize

LogEntry - add the text specified to the log window
\layout Itemize

Python - execute the text specified in the built-in Python interpreter
\layout Standard

If you are not using a Trash folder, it is a good idea to add a rule at
